# Privacy Policy

Effective date: May 25, 2026

Clean It Up! (“we”, “our”, or “us”) respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how information is handled when you use the Clean It Up! mobile game.

## Information We Collect

Clean It Up! does not require you to create an account and does not ask you to provide personal information such as your name, email address, phone number, or address.

The game may use third-party services that collect limited information automatically, such as device information, advertising identifiers, app activity, crash data, diagnostics, and purchase-related information. This information is used to support ads, in-app purchases, app performance, fraud prevention, and service reliability.

## Third-Party Services

Clean It Up! may use the following third-party services:

- Google AdMob, for showing ads
- Google Play Billing, for processing in-app purchases such as removing ads
- Google Play services, for app distribution, purchase validation, and platform functionality

These services may collect and process data according to their own privacy policies.

Google Privacy Policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy

## Advertising

Clean It Up! may display ads. Advertising partners may use device identifiers and similar technologies to show ads, limit ad frequency, measure ad performance, and prevent fraud.

Depending on your region and device settings, you may be able to limit ad personalization through your Android or Google account settings.

## In-App Purchases

Clean It Up! may offer in-app purchases, including an option to remove ads. Purchases are processed by Google Play Billing. We do not receive or store your payment card details.

## Children’s Privacy

Clean It Up! is designed to be family-friendly. We do not knowingly collect personal information directly from children. However, third-party services such as advertising or billing providers may process limited data as described in their own privacy policies.

If you believe a child has provided personal information to us, please contact us so we can take appropriate action.

## Data Sharing

We do not sell personal information. Data may be processed by third-party services used in the game, such as advertising, billing, analytics, crash reporting, or platform services, where applicable.

## Data Security

We take reasonable steps to protect information handled through the game and the services it uses. However, no method of electronic storage or transmission is completely secure.

## Your Choices

You can uninstall the game at any time to stop further data collection by the app.

You may also manage advertising preferences through your device settings or Google account settings.

## Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated effective date.

